content:
When a new message arrives in Messaging, it appears in the Omni-Channel utility or sidebar. To accept a message and open the messaging session window, click the checkmark icon.

To see the first message that a customer sent, hover your mouse over the checkmark icon. The first message can give you context about why the customer is contacting your company.

To send a message to the customer, enter your message and press Enter on your keyboard. Use the lookup fields on the Details tab to associate the session with a case, lead, or opportunity.

This article applies to Messaging for In-App, Messaging for Web, standard and enhanced WhatsApp, standard and enhanced Facebook Messenger, standard and enhanced SMS, enhanced Apple Messages for Business, and Bring Your Own Channel.
title: Accepting Customer Messages in Service Cloud
